title: X-Bow to demonstrate additive manufacturing of solid rocket motors for U.S. Air Force
summary: The U.S. Air Force Research Laboratory awarded X-Bow Systems, a startup that specializes in solid rocket propulsion, a $17.8 million contract to demonstrate additive manufacturing technologies.

title: SpaceX wins first Pentagon contract for Starshield, its satellite network for military use
summary: The Pentagon has awarded Elon Musk’s SpaceX its first confirmed contract for the Starshield network it’s developing, a military-specific version of the company’s Starlink satellite internet system, the defense agency said Wednesday.

title: Rogue Space Systems gets US Air Force funds to advance in-orbit servicing tech
summary: Rogue Space Systems, a three-year-old startup with plans for a fleet of small in-orbit servicing spacecraft, announced more U.S. government funding Sept. 27 to develop core technologies.

title: FAA closes investigation into Blue Origin rocket failure, requires 21 ‘corrective actions’
summary: The Federal Aviation Administration closed its investigation into last year’s failed flight of a cargo mission by Jeff Bezos’ Blue Origin, the regulator announced on Wednesday.

title: ESA to Publish Vega C Test Z40 Test Failure Findings This Week

An ESA Independent Inquiry Commission established to investigate the failure of the Vega C Zerfiro 40 (Z40) static fire test will report its findings before the end of the week.
